reviews.text:
I visit my friend Jon frequently who lives in the area and I make sure to get some delicious pizza from Baby Jakes. It's some of the best pizza I've ever had.
Super fresh ingredients and the people working there are genuine and extremely nice.  Highly highly recommend!!! This will forever be my go to pizza place when I'm in the area.

1st time trying it out and being pizza lovers we will be back. Son and I love the real pepperoni with the spice. Sauce was good and overall flavor good. Only downfall for us is we will ask for it to be more well done next time which is solely a preference. We felt the amount of mushrooms & pepperoni could of been a bit more for the price. Bread sticks were good, next time we will try the cheese sauce instead of the garlic butter. Overall would recommend to others and we will be back again, thank you again.

The Gluten Free Pizza and Cheese Bread was AMAZING! It‚Äôs been so long since I had a nice thick slice of pizza. 1000% recommend. I love the fact the price includes up to 4 toppings, making it super easy to customize your pizza for your preferences. We will definitely be ordering from Baby Jake‚Äôs again!

Great pizza, ordered their kitchen sink. which has several toppings. Perfectly made, dough cooked just right, taste amazing. They also have a gluten free crust option that taste pretty good. The staff are pleasant and friendly too.

I've been here 3 times within a month and must say that this is now one of my favorites for pizza! The pizza is quality and they aren't greedy with toppings. You can choose your crust flavor as well. The cheesy bread is fantastic and filling. Service is great and pizzas are ready in about 20 minutes. Perfect amount of wait time to get an ice cream cone next door.
